dr larry godfrey who was senior medical 
officer investigating the january 1986 explosion of the space 
shuttle challenger has been hired as montanas new state chief 
medical examiner 
the announcement tuesday by attorney general mike greely ends a 
15month national search for someone to replace ron rivers who 
resigned to become chief medical examiner for san diego calif 
godfrey 39 a nationally recognized expert in aircraft accident 
investigations helped conduct the probe into the january 1986 
deaths of the seven challenger astronauts 
he holds the rank of major in the us army medical corps 
