texas sen lloyd bentsens moderate record 
over 24 years in congress makes him a relatively tough target for 
critics as he sets out to carry the democratic vicepresidential 
standard 
but on some issues including the highprofile matter of us 
policy toward nicaragua he is at odds with the man who chose him 
michael dukakis 
himself a millionaire businessman bentsen has consistently 
backed favorable tax treatment for businesses particularly his 
homestate oil industry and believes in minimizing governments 
regulatory hand on industry 
he has been hawkish when it comes to supporting weapons 
programs backing the modernization of us nuclear capability by 
voting for systems such as the mx missile and b1 bomber 
those conservative stances have been balanced by a strong civil 
rights record and by positions in favor of pension reform 
permitting housewives to establish individual retirement accounts 
and providing prenatal care for poor pregnant women he also has 
supported the supreme court decision that legalized abortion 
bentsen also has been behind some of the democrats most potent 
political issues this year the trade bill including a provision 
requiring worker notification of impending plant closings and 
protection against costs of catastrophic health care 
lloyd bentsen is a centrist democrat said oilstate 
colleague sen j bennett johnston dla all democrats supported 
his trade bill and supported his tax policies he builds a 
coalition hes not out on the fringe 
he is out of step with his campaign partner however on one 
matter that leaped into the headlines this week us relations 
with nicaragua 
bentsen like many other southern democrats has supported the 
administrations policy of giving weapons to the contra rebels to 
put military pressure on the leftist managua government dukakis is 
a staunch opponent of the policy calling instead for nonmilitary 
solutions to the countrys political schism 
senate leaders rescheduled a defense money bill which had been 
expected to come to the floor this week until after the democratic 
convention in part because an anticipated contra military aid 
amendment would have highlighted the disagreement between the two 
men at a time when the united states and nicaragua have expelled 
each others top diplomats and plunged relations even further into 
the deep freeze 
also bentsen has favored allowing prayer in public schools 
imposing fees on imported oil and passing a constitutional 
amendment to balance the federal budget and he voted for reagans 
1981 tax cuts and he supports the death penalty dukakis is on the 
opposite side of each of those issues 
politically the mix has helped bentsen thrive in a state where 
ronald reagan won big victories in 1980 and 1984 and where 
democratic influence has waned in recent years his strength has 
helped him build a respected statewide organization in texas and 
become congress most successful fundraiser 
the federal election commission says bentsen in the 15 months 
ending march 31 raised more than 5 million toward his senate 
reelection bid of that amount 146 million was in 
specialinterest money more than any other congressional candidate 
that the bentsen record and organization lend strength to the 
democratic ticket seemed to be indirectly supported by the comments 
of conservative republicans who preferred tuesday to ignore the 
texan and instead aim their barbs at the likely presidential 
nominee 
i dont think republicans are going to be running against 
lloyd bentsen said gop sen phil gramm another texan 
republicans are going to be running against michael dukakis the 
distinctions are just so clear that bentsen is not an issue 
bentsen has for the most part avoided personal controversy 
during his sixyear house stint beginning in 1949 and during his 
three senate terms the most notable recent exception was his 
establishment of a 10000perperson breakfast club for lobbyists 
last year after he took over as chairman of the taxwriting senate 
finance committee he disbanded the effort as soon as it became 
public acknowledging a doozy of a mistake 
despite dukakis rejection of presidential runnerup jesse 
jackson for the no 2 spot on the ticket civil rights advocates 
were generally positive on bentsens record 
one of his first votes after being elected to the house in 1948 
was to oppose the poll tax considered a courageous move for a 
firstterm southerner and bentsen tells of making a hotel he owned 
in houston the first integrated hotel in the city said ralph neas 
executive director of the leadership conference on civil rights 
bentsen is a sponsor of fair housing legislation and voted for 
the civil rights restoration bill an extension of the voting 
rights act and for the bill making martin luther kings birthday a 
holiday neas noted 
it might almost be said that bentsen takes moderation to an 
extreme in 1986 he was given perfect middleofthe road voting 
ratings of 50 percent by both the liberal aflcio and the american 
conservative union 
last year according to a voting analysis by congressional 
quarterly bentsen supported president reagan on 47 percent of 
issues on which the white house announced a position and opposed 
the president 50 percent of the time 
on matters where party unity was a key to the outcome bentsen 
sided with fellow democrats 78 percent of the time a figure 
roughly midway between the partys high of 95 percent and the low 
of 50 percent 
