callers to a detroit radio talk show criticized hayden and his 
wife jane fonda for their antivietnam war activities more of 
the same came from about a dozen veterans who protested outside a 
hall in warren where hayden appeared 
hayden said his home state figured prominently in his book he 
and other activists founded students for a democratic society in 
1962 in port huron mich 
the book also describes the end of 14 years of estrangement from 
his father jack hayden who died the night hayden was elected to 
the california assembly in 1982 hayden said haydens mother died 
in 1986 
as best i can sort it out i wrote the book first out of 
compulsion to find out something about myself and my parents 
hayden said 
</TEXT>
