the journal providence ri on the shortage of tuba players 
we possess no statistics to bolster our impression but the word 
is out that america will soon be suffering from a serious shortage 
of tuba players 
the present situation is said to be influenced by a perceived 
decline in musical training among the young as well as the cost of 
the instrument which is measured in the thousands of dollars 
another obvious factor is sound the tuba sounds very much 
as it looks which is not especially elegant what the tuba does 
do well however is furnish a fullbodied sound to a band or 
orchestra a sound without which many major works are rendered 
simply shadows of themselves 
if tuba lovers want to demonstrate the importance of the 
survival of their instrument they need only play a sousa march 
first without then with the endangered tuba the difference is 
astounding 
</TEXT>
