<TEXT>
in a region where concern about terrorism 
is high and the profile of american military personnel low us 
experts investigating the shooting down of an iranian airliner are 
silent and nearly invisible 
their daily travels between a manama hotel and two us warships 
anchored off bahrain are quick and discreet they wear civilian 
clothes while ashore as do other us military personnel in the 
securityconscious arab countries of the persian gulf 
the sixman team arrived july 5 on a special us military 
aircraft two days after the iran air airbus a300 was shot down by 
the missile cruiser uss vincennes which mistook it for an iranian 
f14 fighter all 290 people aboard were killed 
a 15day period allowed for completion of the report is more 
than half gone but officials at us central command headquarters 
in tampa fla say it can be extended if rear adm william m 
fogarty the team leader decides more time is needed 
