determine female representation in the two industries and whether 
there are overt or subtle pressures against hiring or promoting 
women ms mclaughlin said 
women filled about 12 percent of construction jobs in 1980 
according to census figures that year when government and industry 
set goals to increase the proportion to 69 percent over the next 
few years said labor department aide jerry blakemore so far he 
said womens representation in contruction jobs has improved only 
to about 2 percent 
