blacks and whites on many 
commuter trains rode together wednesday for the first time and a 
parliament member urged the government to extend integration to 
buses and intercity trains 
the whites only signs on firstclass train coaches started 
coming down tuesday in the johannesburg and durban metropolitan 
areas but many riders did not learn of the change until wednesday 
commuter trains in the cape town area were desegregated last 
month 
from now on segregation will be based only on economic 
principles said jc van der merwe railroad manager in 
transvaal province for the staterun south african transport 
services 
