wednesday reported some unfriendly looks from white passengers but 
there were no reports of serious incidents 
one white woman who spoke on condition of anonymity said a 
black man sat beside her during her morning ride into johannesburg 
and asked if she would be back on the train the next day when she 
replied affirmatively the man inquired are you going to learn 
xhosa 
xhosa is one of the four main african languages in south africa 
the transport service began integrating restrooms waiting 
areas railroad cafeterias and other amenities at train stations in 
1985 most coaches continued to be segregated according to race 
although a few firstclass trains were declared open to all 
firstclass tickets cost about twice as much as thirdclass 
tickets there is no secondclass service 
