all would be ready by the time the opening gavel fell next monday 
ready perhaps but not necessarily peaceful 
dukakis and bentsen received a rousing reception from house 
democrats when they met early in the day he sent one single 
message said rep ron wyden dore he wants to work with us 
and reach out to us thats what the congress wants to hear 
others were finding their disappointment harder to overcome 
jackson said nothing publicly during the day about dukakis 
choice of the 67yearold bentsen to be his vice presidential 
candidate 
but campaign aide brown spread the word that the runnerup in 
the primary campaign was incredulous that dukakis had not consulted 
him over the choice of bentsen and had not informed him before the 
word was made public 
it seems like too big a mistake that politically astute people 
would make said brown 
he said negotiations over platform disagreements have been 
suspended at least temporarily 
privately some were urging jackson not to overreact to the 
perceived snub i dont think its in jesses interest to get 
into a fight about protocol and have his constituents talking 
about no respect no respect said one influential black 
politician 
what if dukakis loses and people can point to this episode as 
one of the reasons then jesse has just kicked over his pail of 
milk 
