members of a house panel examining health 
hazards caused by lead in drinkingwater coolers accused an 
illinois manufacturer on wednesday of stonewalling their 
investigation 
reps henry waxman dcalif and gerry sikorski dminn said 
halsey taylor of freeport ill should quit denying in the face of 
contradictory evidence that it made coolers containing lead and 
recall any of its products which might be contaminated 
the demands came at a hearing of the house energy and commerce 
subcommittee on health and the environment which waxman chairs on 
sikorskis bill to eradicate lead from school drinkingwater 
supplies 
lead is a poison that damages the brain kidneys and other 
organs it is particularly hazardous to growing children 
we have never intentionally manufactured any cooler with a 
lead lining or lead materials inside the tank robin g munden 
the companys lawyer told the subcommittee we have carefully 
examined manufacturing records going back to 1920 and there is not 
a single mention of lead materials or lead lining on any of those 
tanks 
however waxman said that in tests last year of 20 coolers used 
by the navy the environmental protection agency found eight of 12 
halsey taylor units had tanks lined with leadbased solder 
he said water from one halsey taylor cooler tested was 
contaminated with lead at concentrations of 2000 parts per 
billion 40 times the current federal drinkingwater standard and 
100 times the standard epa is expected to adopt later this year 
we havent yet been able to confirm that the epa tests were 
accurate munden said assuming they were we dont know what 
the source of the lead in those tanks was when weve had an 
opportunity to confirm that then well have an explanation 
he said halsey taylor a subsidiary of household international 
inc and one of the nations largest manufacturers of water 
coolers will act responsibly if independent tests showed the 
company was at fault 
how do you take responsibility if you deny responsibility in 
the face of evidence waxman said during an exchange with munden 
how are you taking responsibility simply by stonewalling a 
committee of congress when the facts have been established by the 
environmental protection agency 
we have not deliberately or indirectly misled this 
committee the lawyer replied we believe halsey taylor tanks 
are safe 
holding up half a tank from a halsey taylor cooler sikorski 
said it had a uniform lead lining which could not have come from 
what the company suggested might be a pinhole leak caused by 
manufacturing error and demanded they come clean 
letting your kid drink from one of these is like handing her a 
glass of lead koolaid he said until they clean up their act 
i wont drink a drop of water from a halsey taylor cooler 
sikorski said his bill would require the immediate 
identification and recall of all leadcontaminated coolers and 
would hold the manufacturer responsible for all costs 
