azerbaijan quashed a territorys attempt to secede 
and join armenia tass reported wednesday creating another 
stalemate in an ethnic dispute that has caused months of turmoil in 
the two southern republics 
the official news agency said the presidium or executive 
committee of azerbaijans parliament met tuesday night and 
declared null and void the declaration of secession that the 
nagornokarabakh legislature passed tuesday 
threequarters of nagornokarabakhs 160000 residents are 
ethnic armenians but the enclave was made part of azerbaijan in 
1923 the argument over it became public in february and the two 
neighboring caucasus republics have been disrupted by riots 
strikes and huge demonstrations 
tass quoted the azerbaijan presidiums resolution as saying the 
territorys legislature failed to secure strict compliance with 
principles of legality and openly encroached on the 
nationalstate composition of the republic 
it said only 101 of the 150 legislators were present when 
secession was voted reporters for the radio station in the 
territorial capital stepanakert said tuesday the vote was 
unanimous except for one abstention 
vladimir v vaselenko prosecutor of nagornokarabakh said in 
an interview broadcast by soviet television wednesday that the 
legislatures action violated the constitutions and laws of 
