free legal help from an atlanta law firm 
a 24hour hotline operated by the firm of federal amp todd will 
provide credentialcarrying reporters with free legal advice and 
representation if needed while covering the convention 
the hotline arranged by the reporters committee with the 
cooperation of the atlanta bureau of police services is intended 
to minimize problems faced by reporters covering demonstrations or 
other newsworthy events 
mass arrests have occasionally resulted from major disturbances 
during past political conventions and journalists have been taken 
into custody 
