conway delayed ruling on the motion to exclude evidence saying 
he wanted to study the matter he told attorneys to be ready with 
opening statements thursday morning 
remerthamert 44 was indicted on nine counts of conspiracy 
transporting and harboring illegal aliens and mail fraud the 
latter charge in connection with the adoption of one of the 
salvadoran womens babies ms martinez 28 was charged with four 
counts of transporting and inducing illegal aliens 
conway said he was concerned about admitting into evidence a 
letter allegedly written by venturarivas in november 1986 and 
delivered by remerthamert to one of the salvadoran women in 
albuquerque conway noted the indictment charges the defendants 
with a conspiracy that ended aug 28 1986 but the letter was 
written months later 
he also said he had problems extending any alleged conspiracy 
between remerthamert and venturarivas to include ms martinez 
us attorney william lutz argued that statements from 
venturarivas should be allowed because they could be corroborated 
with other evidence but defense attorney karen snell of san 
francisco called that evidence hearsay 
the only person to testify at the threehour hearing was mike 
murphy a us immigration and naturalization service investigator 
who described what the salvadoran women told him about their trip 
into the united states in august 1986 
the women cecelia eliasalegria and inez camposanzora were 
not in court wednesday although they remain in the united states 
and are expected to be called as prosecution witnesses 
