<TEXT>
the dream of home ownership which once 
seemed almost a right to most californians is slipping ever 
farther from firsttime buyers as prices explode far beyond the 
limits of the average pocketbook 
the states desirable climate and strong economy have long 
pushed housing demand and prices ahead of the national average but 
nowadays wouldbe home buyers are finding it difficult to come up 
with even a down payment 
statistics show why the median cost of a california home 
reached 160073 in may nearly double the national median of 
88600 and 134 percent higher than the median california home 
price a year ago 
just 28 percent of the states households could afford that 
averagepriced home in may according to figures provided by the 
california association of realtors nationally 48 percent of 
households can afford the median level home 
we really want to be in a house this year and were going to 
go into debt to our ears to do it said tim dressendorfer a 
locksmith who once thought he and his wife could find a reasonable 
starter home for 150000 in the long beach area 
after six months they are still searching and are now 
considering taking out a variableinterest loan rather than a 
fixedrate mortgage so they can borrow more money 
the latest state realtors figures show orange county with the 
highest median home price tag in the state 202760 the average 
30year mortgage with a 20percent down payment on that house would 
require monthly payments of 1565 the trade group says 
even in affluent orange county only 22 percent of households 
earn the 62611 a year needed to qualify for such a mortgage 
its just so hard to save as much money as you need so your 
payments arent ridiculous said michelle st john 26 who rents 
a home in riverside with her husband judd 
many people sacrifice typically with a longer commute 
commonly two to four hours round trip in the los angeles area to a 
home in distant suburbs where prices are lower 
the old option of asking mom and dad for help has been 
supplemented these days by brokers who match investors with 
potential home buyers who need a down payment the young couple 
live in the house and share the home title with their equity 
partner who shares any resale profits 
just how fast are prices rising in recent months buyers of 
homes in desirable sections and suburbs of los angeles have found 
themselves in bidding wars for their dream houses paying far above 
listed price 
