department estimated this years corn production would fall more 
than 26 percent below last year to a 5year low based on current 
crop conditions the usda said soybean production probably would 
decline by at least 14 percent from last years 19 billion bushels 
many analysts had called the estimates conservative and were 
expecting a less dramatic reaction from traders 
i guess their enthusiasm picked up after they had a chance to 
sleep on it said jerry gidel an analyst in chicago with the 
trading firm gh miller amp co 
